---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Limitations" description="What HeadGenome does not claim. Known constraints on current results.">
<div class="page-top">
  <p class="eyebrow">Limitations & Open Questions</p>
  <h1>What we<br/>don't claim.</h1>
  <p class="lead">A visible limitations section is a credibility signal. These are real constraints on the current results.</p>
</div>
<div class="section">
  <div class="limit-list">
    {[
      { n: '01', title: 'Models up to 1.5B parameters', body: 'All causal ablation and KV-cache experiments were run on models ≤ 1.5B parameters. Whether the same four-class taxonomy holds at 7B, 70B, or 400B is an open empirical question. The V/Q scaling law appears in every architecture we tested, but extrapolation to frontier-scale models is untested.' },
      { n: '02', title: 'FLOP savings are FLOP-model projections', body: 'The 4–8× FLOP savings numbers are FLOP-model projections — mathematically grounded in real measured head fractions, not measured wall-clock speedups. Realising these projections requires a sparse kernel backend (FlexAttention or custom CUDA). The 13.3× KV-cache compression was directly measured on Llama-3.2-1B hardware.' },
      { n: '03', title: 'Rare head counts are small', body: 'Retrieval heads are rare (1–13 per model). Statistical conclusions about Retrieval head behaviour rest on small within-architecture sample sizes. Cross-architecture consistency is strong, but within-architecture variance estimates have wide confidence intervals.' },
      { n: '04', title: 'Hyper-diagonal heads are unresolved', body: 'A small number of heads (~1–2% in GPT-2 Medium) sit at the boundary between Local and Retrieval. These exhibit context-dependent switching between local and global attention patterns. They are classified as Local by our probe but may warrant a fifth class in a more refined taxonomy.' },
      { n: '05', title: 'KV geometry is qualitative', body: 'The PCA projections in Figure 12 are a qualitative illustration, not a quantitative proof. PCA explained variance is typically 30–55% in 3D. The untrained-control panel is the key control, but positional encoding contamination of the projection cannot be fully ruled out.' },
      { n: '06', title: 'GQA head-indexing caveat', body: 'For GQA models (Qwen, Llama), KV-cache head indices map to KV-groups, not individual query heads. Our analysis correctly maps through the group structure (kv_head = query_head // group_size), but the effective granularity is coarser in GQA architectures than in MHA architectures like GPT-2.' },
    ].map(l => (
      <div class="limit-item reveal">
        <span class="limit-n">{l.n}</span>
        <div>
          <h3>{l.title}</h3>
          <p>{l.body}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
</Layout>

<style>
.section { max-width:820px; margin:0 auto; padding:3rem 2.5rem 8rem; }
.limit-list { display:flex; flex-direction:column; }
.limit-item {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
  gap: 0 1.5rem; padding: 2.5rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  align-items: start;
}
.limit-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.limit-n { font-size: .7rem; font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--text-3); padding-top: .2rem; }
.limit-item h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
.limit-item p { font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text-2); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
</style>
